article.description:
Center Margo Dydek scored 22 points to lead the
Utah Starzz to a 71-68 victory over the Seattle Storm on Sunday
night.
article.headline: Starzz now 4-0 on Storm's home court
article.linkText: Dydek scores 22 as Utah wins again in Seattle
article.story:
SEATTLE (AP) -- Center Margo Dydek scored 22 points to lead the
Utah Starzz to a 71-68 victory over the Seattle Storm on Sunday
night.

	   Adrienne Goodson added 14 points and four assists for Utah
(4-2), while Marie Ferdinand scored 13 points.

	   The Storm got as close as 68-66 with just less than a minute to go,
but Jennifer Azzi hit a 3-pointer with 10.3 seconds left to seal
the victory.

	   ''We heard them call zone and we just always have to be ready
for the shot when Marie penetrates,'' Azzi said. ''That was nice.
Those open shots are few and far between.''

	   Natalie Williams added 13 points as the Starzz, who improved to
4-0 overall in Key Arena.

	   ''Each team brings out the best and worse of each other,''
Starzz head coach Candi Harvey said. ''We always have great
basketball games here in Seattle.''

	   Lauren Jackson had 16 points and five blocked shots for Seattle
(3-2) in her first action of the season. The No. 1
overall draft choice last season and the WNBA's rookie of the year missed the
Storm's first four games with a sprained ankle.

	   Jackson and Dydek got tangled up going for a rebound with 9:22
to play. The two didn't separate until Jackson had thrown an elbow
into Dydek's back and was charged with a technical foul.

	   ''She's a dirty player and does some crazy stuff out there,''
Dydek said.

	   Jackson saw it differently.

	   ''She got me in the back,'' Jackson said. ''I got the technical
for swearing, not for anything I did out there to her.''

	   Sue Bird, the No. 1 overall choice this season who came into the game
averaging 19 points for the Storm, finished with seven points.

	   Semeka Randall scored Seattle's first 13 points to start the
second half and finished with 21 points, while reserve Jamie Redd
had 14.

	   Seattle opened the game with a 16-9 run with Jackson scoring 10
points, including two 3-pointers.

	   With Jackson on the bench with three fouls, Utah took its first
lead at 5:28 of the first half. Dydek scored 12 points in the run
as the Starzz went up 28-22. She also pulled down nine rebounds as
Utah took a 32-30 halftime lead.
